methods.bs:
Getter for the byte slice.

:return: io.deephaven.csv.containers.ByteSlice
methods.isExhausted:
Is the iteration exhausted? This is set to true when tryMoveNext() is called and returns false.

:return: (boolean) Whether the iteration is exhausted.
methods.numConsumed:
Number of items we've consumed so far. This is the number of times tryMoveNext() has been called and
 returned true.

:return: (long) The number of items we've consumed so far
methods.tryMoveNext:
Try to advance to the next (or very first) item.

:return: (boolean) true if we were able to advance, and set bs to valid text. Otherwise false.

text:
This class is used to hold the underlying DenseStorageReader plus some associated helper information (an
 allocated ByteSlice for slice storage, plus a couple helpful statistics like numConsumed and
 isExhausted.
